(Amazon RDS) Overview.

3
00:00:05,060 --> 00:00:08,710
Amazon RDS is a managed relational database service.

4
00:00:08,860 --> 00:00:11,390
Amazon RDS makes it easy to set up,

5
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:14,540
operate, and scale a relational database in the cloud.

6
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:18,050
It provides cost-efficient and resizable capacity while

7
00:00:18,050 --> 00:00:20,480
automating time-consuming administration tasks

8
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,040
such as hardware provisioning,

9
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:24,640
database setup, patching, and backups.

10
00:00:25,340 --> 00:00:27,970
It frees you to focus on your applications.

11
00:00:27,980 --> 00:00:32,330
Amazon RDS provides you with six familiar database engines to choose from,

12
00:00:32,340 --> 00:00:34,040
including Amazon Aurora,

13
00:00:34,050 --> 00:00:40,220
PostgreSQL, MySQL, MariaDB, Oracle Database, and SQL Server.

14
00:00:40,870 --> 00:00:44,020
You can use the AWS Database Migration Service to

15
